A '''timing or valve chest''' is a compartment on an internal or external [[internal combustion engine|combustion engine]] (e.g. gasoline or [[steam engine]]) which provides access to the [[tappet]]s and valves. The chest is fitted with an inspection cover sealed with a [[gasket]].

